relationships.description: Chett conspired to kill Lord Commander Mormont, though the mutiny unfolded differently with others doing the deed.
relationships.evidence: We need to kill all the officers, I say... The Old Bear dies... That's all. We kill them quiet, while they sleep.

relationships.description: Brienne escorts Jaime to King's Landing, protecting him along the way.
relationships.evidence: I am delivering you to King's Landing... You are under my protection.

relationships.description: Vargo Hoat orders Zollo to cut off Jaime Lannister's hand, maiming him (though not killing him).
relationships.evidence: The goat... losing his sword hand to the blade of Zollo the Fat.

relationships.description: Tyrion and Sansa are forced to marry.
relationships.evidence: I do solemnly proclaim Tyrion of House Lannister and Sansa of House Stark to be man and wife.

relationships.description: Catelyn is the mother of Robb Stark.
relationships.evidence: Mother... I have a new daughter... my lady wife.

relationships.description: Walder Frey orchestrates the Red Wedding where Robb Stark is killed.
relationships.evidence: Roose Bolton... thrust his longsword through her son's heart... Lord Walder... sat on his carved oaken throne, watching greedily.

relationships.description: Roose Bolton personally kills Robb Stark at the Red Wedding.
relationships.evidence: Jaime Lannister sends his regards. He thrust his longsword through her son's heart, and twisted.

relationships.description: Olenna Tyrell (implied) poisons Joffrey at the wedding feast.
relationships.evidence: I dreamt of a maid at a feast with purple serpents in her hair, venom dripping from their fangs... The Queen of Thorns... straightened Sansa's hair net.

relationships.description: Littlefinger rescues Sansa from King's Landing and takes her to the Vale.
relationships.evidence: Come to the godswood tonight if you want to go home... It had to be the godswood.

relationships.description: Littlefinger pushes Lysa Arryn out the Moon Door.
relationships.evidence: Only Cat. He gave her a short, sharp shove. Lysa stumbled backward... And then she was gone.

relationships.description: Tyrion shoots Tywin with a crossbow in the privy.
relationships.evidence: The crossbow whanged... You shot me... Do me a kindness now, and die quickly.

relationships.description: Tyrion strangles Shae in his father's bed.
relationships.evidence: Tyrion slid a hand under his father's chain, and twisted... He gave cold hands another twist as the warm ones beat away his tears.

relationships.description: Stannis defeats Mance Rayder's wildling army at the Wall.
relationships.evidence: Stannis landed his knights at Eastwatch... He smashed them. Mance Rayder was taken captive.
You're mine, she whispered. Mine, as I'm yours.

relationships.description: Ygritte is killed during the attack on Castle Black (Jon finds her dying).
relationships.evidence: He found Ygritte sprawled across a patch of old snow... You know nothing, Jon Snow, she sighed, dying.

relationships.description: Daenerys banishes Jorah for his past betrayal.
relationships.evidence: You are banished, ser... If you're found in Meereen past break of day, I will have Strong Belwas twist your head off.

relationships.description: Oberyn fights Gregor. Gregor kills Oberyn, but Oberyn's poisoned spear leaves Gregor dying.
relationships.evidence: The Red Viper of Dorne... smashed her fucking head in... The spearhead went through... The flesh mortifies and the wounds ooze pus.

relationships.description: Samwell manipulates the election to make Jon Snow Lord Commander.
relationships.evidence: Sam did it! You're not the ones who got chosen as the nine-hundredth-and-ninety-eighth Lord Commander.
